17/11/2002
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Yugoslavia -- Acting Yugoslav Army Chief of General Staff Lt Gen Branko Krga met with KFOR commander Lt Gen Fabio Mini on Friday (15 November), focusing on co-operation on security matters in Kosovo.
They toured the Merdare base, inspecting personnel and living conditions.
In other news, the new Pristina municipal council took an oath before representatives of the international community Thursday.
The new administration consists of 51 members, including three representatives of the Serbian population and one representing the Turkish population.
(Tanjug, B92 Radio and TV - 15/11/02;
KosovaLive - 14/11/02)
